REFERENCE   1  (bases 1 to 5637)
  AUTHORS   Qiu,H.B., Sun,W.D., Yang,X., Jiang,Q.Y., Chen,S. and Lin,D.G.
  TITLE     Promoter mutation and reduced expression of BRCA1 in canine mammary
            tumors
  JOURNAL   Res Vet Sci 103, 143-148 (2015)
   PUBMED   26679809
  REMARK    GeneRIF: 46.7% of the malignant mammary tumors were found with a
            deletion of one cytosine in the promoter region. mRNA expression of
            BRCA1 was significantly reduced in benign and malignant mammary
            tumors.
REFERENCE   2  (bases 1 to 5637)
  AUTHORS   Sun,W., Yang,X., Qiu,H., Zhang,D., Wang,H., Huang,J. and Lin,D.
  TITLE     Relationship between three novel SNPs of BRCA1 and canine mammary
            tumors
  JOURNAL   J Vet Med Sci 77 (11), 1541-1543 (2015)
   PUBMED   26156012
  REMARK    GeneRIF: Three previously unreported single-nucleotide
            polymorphisms in BRCA1 in canine mammary tumors are reported.
REFERENCE   3  (bases 1 to 5637)
  AUTHORS   Enginler,S.O., Akis,I., Toydemir,T.S., Oztabak,K., Haktanir,D.,
            Gunduz,M.C., Kirsan,I. and Firat,I.
  TITLE     Genetic variations of BRCA1 and BRCA2 genes in dogs with mammary
            tumours
  JOURNAL   Vet Res Commun 38 (1), 21-27 (2014)
   PUBMED   24122022
  REMARK    GeneRIF: one SNP in exon 9 of BRCA1 and one SNP in exon 24 of BRCA2
            were found to be significantly associated with canine mammary
            tumours
REFERENCE   4  (bases 1 to 5637)
  AUTHORS   Rivera,P., Melin,M., Biagi,T., Fall,T., Haggstrom,J.,
            Lindblad-Toh,K. and von Euler,H.
  TITLE     Mammary tumor development in dogs is associated with BRCA1 and
            BRCA2
  JOURNAL   Cancer Res 69 (22), 8770-8774 (2009)
   PUBMED   19887619
  REMARK    GeneRIF: this study indicates that BRCA1 and BRCA2 contribute to
            the risk of canine mammary tumors in English springer spaniels
REFERENCE   5  (bases 1 to 5637)
  AUTHORS   Sugiura,T., Matsuyama,S., Akiyosi,H., Takenaka,S., Yamate,J.,
            Kuwamura,M., Aoki,M., Shimada,T., Ohashi,F. and Kubo,K.
  TITLE     Expression patterns of the BRCA1 splicing variants in canine normal
            tissues and mammary gland tumors
  JOURNAL   J Vet Med Sci 69 (6), 587-592 (2007)
   PUBMED   17611353
  REMARK    GeneRIF: The expression of multiple splice variants of BRCA1 in
            mammary gland tumors of dogs is reported.
REFERENCE   6  (bases 1 to 5637)
  AUTHORS   Gray,I.S. and Yuzbasiyan-Gurkan,V.
  TITLE     A single nucleotide (T-->G) polymorphism within intron 23 of the
